<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ROK President Kim on DPRK Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0301143394 Beijing XINHUA in English 1426 GMT 3 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0301143394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, January 3 (XINHUA) -- South Korean President 
Kim Yong-sam has said that the crucial nuclear issue in the 
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) must be solved this 
year, as it is vital for the survival of the entire peninsula. 
  "The North Korean nuclear problem, which is of ultimate 
importance to the survival of the 70 million Korean people, 
should be solved early this year at the latest," Kim said at a 
new year's ceremony in the presidential residence here Monday. 
  "We have many difficulties trying to solve the nuclear issue 
and we need inter-Korean negotiations," he said. 
  On the same day, Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu said that 
South Korea is getting ready for the day when neighboring 
countries recognize the DPRK and normalize their relations with 
Pyongyang, as is likely to happen this year. 
  "We shall think about our practical interests and the 
people's feelings, and we plan to gradually develop government 
positions to prepare for talks on normalizing diplomatic 
relations between North Korea and neighboring countries," Han 
told reporters. 
  Han's comments came as the DPRK and the United States near 
agreement on resuming high-level talks to untangle Pyongyang's 
nuclear problem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-44413 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi002_q_94001" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-002 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  4 Jan 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Southwest Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sichuan Secretary Addresses Deng Study Class </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK3112134093 Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 22 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> HK3112134093 </F>
<F P=104>  Chengdu Sichuan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] County party committee secretaries in Sichuan wound 
up the latest round of collective study in Chengdu yesterday. 
Provincial party committee Secretary Xie Shijie yesterday 
attended and relayed the spirit of the sixth provincial party 
committee second plenary session at the study class at which 
provincial party committee Deputy Secretary Qin Yuqin also made 
a speech. 
  Secretary Xie Shijie pointed out in his speech: The sixth 
provincial party committee second plenary session, which 
concluded on 21 December, had implemented to the letter the 
spirit of the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central 
Committee and the spirit of a recently concluded national 
economic work conference. The important plenary session had also 
made specific arrangements for Sichuan's work in 1994. 
  After briefly reviewing Sichuan's work in 1993, Secretary 
Xie 
Shijie spelled out the following tasks and requirements for 1994: 
  1. To strive to acquire a correct understanding of the 
current situation, enhance a sense of opportunity, press ahead 
with all- round development, and intensify a sense of historical 
responsibility. 
  2. To closely integrate reform, opening up, and 
construction, adopt an overall point of view, concentrate on key 
aspects of work, and quicken the pace of economic development. 
  3. To keep close watch over new developments and new 
problems, continually and firmly grasp two key aspects of work 
at the same time, safeguard social stability, and push ahead 
with social progress and development. 
  Comrade Qin Yuqin stated in his speech: During 15 days of 
theory study, county party committee secretaries from across 
Sichuan have conscientiously studied Volume 3 of the 
Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping, all documents issued 
by the Third Plenary Session of the 14th CPC Central Committee, 
and the spirit of the recently concluded national economic work 
conference. They also listened to a number of work reports and 
scored relatively gratifying results in theory study. Thanks to 
these study activities, all county party committee secretaries 
have now acquired an in-depth understanding of the ideological 
line of emancipating the mind and seeking truth from facts, 
which constitutes the essence of Volume 3 of the Selected 
Works of Deng Xiaoping, as well as the theory of building 
socialism with Chinese characteristics, which constitutes the 
main theme of Volume 3 of the Selected Works of Deng 
Xiaoping. They have also further emancipated their minds, 
successfully removed a variety of ideological obstacles 
hampering Sichuan's development, deepened their understanding of 
such a question as why a socialist market economic structure 
should be built, enhanced comprehension of the basic principle 
underpinning socialism with Chinese characteristics which is 
continually and firmly grasping two key work aspects at the same 
time. 
  Comrade Qin Yuqin also called for continually and profoundly 
studying and conscientiously implementing all strategic tasks 
laid down at the 14th CPC National Congress, further updating 
ideological concepts, and cultivating a fine style among broad 
masses of party members and cadres, especially leading cadres at 
and above the county level, in order that all comrades will 
attach importance to theory study and respect science. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

