<H3> <TI>   Taipei To Hold Cross-Strait Insurance Seminar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401104194 Taipei CNA in English 0907 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401104194 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Y.C. Tsai] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, Jan. 4 (CNA) -- Insurance experts from 
Taiwan and Mainland China will meet in Taipei January 22-25 in a 
bid to strengthen cross-strait insurance cooperation. 
  The three-day forum will be the second of its kind, the 
first 
being held in Beijing and Shanghai in September 1992. 
  A 20-member mainland delegation is expected. It will be the 
first time in more than four decades that mainland Chinese 
insurance experts have visited Taiwan. 
  Sponsored by the National Insurance Institute, the forum 
will 
focus on insurance rules and regulations, future trends, and the 
division of social and business insurance. 

</TEXT>

