<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin's Activities Reported </TI></H3>
<H4>   Inscribes for New Bridge </H4>
<F P=102> OW3112095993 Beijing XINHUA in English 0855 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW3112095993 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Jinan, December 31 (XINHUA) -- After two years' 
work, Dongming Bridge across the Yellow River recently opened to 
traffic in east China's Shandong Province. 
  President Jiang Zemin calligraphed the name-plate for the 
bridge. 
  Located at the juncture of the three provinces of Hebei, 
Shandong and Henan, the 4,142-meter-long bridge ranks second 
among the bridges over the Yellow River. 
  Construction started in October, 1991, and the bridge was 
completed four months ahead of schedule. It cost 235 million 
yuan. 
  The five-arched, big-span box beam in the middle of the 
bridge was joined successfully on its first test run. Experts 
say this is a major breakthrough in the history of China's 
bridge-building. 
  The bridge is of great importance to facilitate the 
exploration of the Zhongyuan oil field and for the region's 
development. 

</TEXT>

