<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Tianjin Secretary Receives Singapore Ambassador </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK0301075794 Tianjin TIANJIN RIBAO in Chinese 23 Dec 93 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK0301075794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tianjin TIANJIN RIBAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Gao Dezhan, secretary of the municipal party 
committee, received Cheng Tong Fatt, ambassador of Singapore in 
China, in the Guoji Building noon on 22 December. 
  During the reception Gao Dezhan said: Tianjin is further 
broadening its program of opening up and accelerating the 
utilization of foreign capital, and cooperating with foreign 
countries in all directions, in multiple fields, and at multiple 
levels. The municipality welcomes investments and projects of 
foreign countries in every corner in the world. 
  Gao Dezhan welcomed the arrival of Ambassador Cheng Tong 
Fatt. He said: Opening the municipality to the outside world 
and utilizing foreign capital represents a fundamental plan for 
the municipality to accelerate its development. Tianjin has 
many land resources and foundations of industry and commerce. 
It also possesses scientific and technological forces and 
convenient air, maritime, and highway transportation 
facilities. Based on existing cooperation with Singapore, we 
are willing to further more extensive, in depth cooperation on a 
larger scale. In order to become one of the country's best, most 
attractive regions for foreign investments, Tianjin must make it 
easy for foreign businessmen and firms to invest their money in 
the municipality, and make things convenient and profitable. We 
welcome Singaporeans to make more fact finding visits in the 
municipality and to learn about the municipal investment 
environment in order to broaden cooperation and exchanges 
between Tianjin and Singapore. 
  Attending the reception were Ye Disheng, vice mayor of the 
municipality, and responsible persons from the departments 
concerned. 

</TEXT>

