<F P=103> OW0401094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, January 4 (XINHUA) -- Thai Princess Maha 
Chakkri Sirinthon left here this morning on a 15-day official 
visit to China. 
  While in China, she will visit Beijing, where she would meet 
Chinese government leaders, and make a trip to northeast China 
to study education and cultural development projects. 
  The princess is interested in the Chinese language, culture, 
traditional painting and customs of the minorities. 

