<F P=100> West Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   NPC's Qiao Shi To Visit West Europe </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401095094 Beijing XINHUA in English 0936 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 4 (XINHUA) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of 
the Standing Committee of China's National People's Congress 
[NPC], will pay an official goodwill visit to Germany, 
Switzerland and Austria from January 16 to 30, at the invitation 
of the Presidium of the Bundestag of Germany, President Gret 
Haller of the National Council of the Federal Assembly of 
Switzerland, and President Heinz Fischer of the National Council 
of Austria. 
  A Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman made the announcement 
here today. 
  This will be the first visit ever paid by the chairman of 
China's NPC Standing Committee to west European countries and 
will be of great importance to promoting China's relations with 
Germany, Switzerland and Austria, the spokesman said. 

