<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Big Efforts' To Increase Farm Production Planned </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3012163193 Beijing XINHUA in English 1606 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW3012163193 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, December 30 (XINHUA) -- China will make 
big efforts to achieve a sustained increase in farm production 
and farmers' incomes, said Liu Jiang, minister of agriculture. 
  In an interview with XINHUA, he said that to meet the demand 
of national economic reform and development in 1994, the reform 
of the farm production structure must be enhanced so as to 
ensure a steady increase in cotton, food and oil production. 
  He also said that efforts should be redoubled to accelerate 
the development of stock breeding, aquatic and vegetable 
production to provide more and better non-staple food for urban 
people. 
  The development of township enterprises should be focused on 
raising economic returns, he added. 
  Liu said that his ministry has made a decision to put into 
full play the role of the ministry's macro economic control, by 
strengthening the building of the information system, improving 
the legal system, expanding capital construction and fostering a 
contingent of people with farming technical skills. 

</TEXT>

