<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Statistical Bureau To Use Data To Serve Farmers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3112100293 Beijing XINHUA in English 0811 GMT 31 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW3112100293 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, December 31 (XINHUA) -- China's state 
statistics bureau will make use of its abilities in collecting 
information and better serve the farmers and township 
enterprises next year. 
  Shao Zongming, deputy director of the bureau, said recently 
that all the statistics organizations will make grass-root 
investigations and provide information for leaders of the party 
and government departments to make decisions and formulate 
policies. 
  The bureau will research how to increase farmers' incomes, 
develop rural markets, further improve the social services 
system for agricultural production and strengthen the 
agricultural foundations. It will also conduct researches on 
the price scissors of industrial and agricultural products and 
monitor the conditions in the socio-economic performance in the 
rural areas. 
  Facing the market economy for only a short time, farmers 
often encounter puzzling difficulties. Shao said that the 
statistical organizations will help them by supplying 
information and guiding their production, so as to protect their 
interests. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

