<H3> <TI>   Chen Junsheng Heads All-China Greening Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3012133893 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1108 
GMT 24 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW3012133893 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, 24 Dec (XINHUA) -- The All-China Greening 
Committee recently formed a new committee, with State Councillor 
Chen Junsheng as chairman. 
  The vice chairmen are: Xu Youfang (minister of forestry), 
Liu Jimin (State Council deputy secretary general), Fu Quanyou 
(director of the General Logistics Department of the Chinese 
People's Liberation Army [PLA]), Chen Yaobang (vice minister of 
the State Planning Commission), Hou Jie (minister of 
construction), Li Yanling (vice minister of finance), and Li 
Qiyan (Beijing Municipal Mayor). 
  The posts of 26 committee members are held by responsible 
persons from relevant departments of the State Council, the 
three PLA general departments, the Headquarters of the Chinese 
People's Armed Police Force, and mass organizations. 

</TEXT>

