<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister of Forestry Views 1994 Plans, Tasks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW3012122593 Beijing XINHUA in English 1048 GMT 30 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> OW3012122593 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, December 30 (XINHUA) -- China is to 
afforest a total of 4.48 million ha and achieve a forestry 
output value of 152 billion yuan in 1994, according to Minister 
of Forestry Xu Youfang. 
  These figures will represent an increase of nine percent 
over 
1993. 
  Xu said that the afforestation work will be linked more 
closely with promoting the rural economy and helping peasants to 
shake off poverty. Forestry should yield environmental and 
social as well as economic returns, xu stressed. 
  To meet next year's target, the minister said, China will 
develop more cash trees and trees for industrial use, while 
continuing the construction of state key forestry projects. 
  China will deepen the reform of the state-run forestry 
centers and promote the development of township and village tree 
farms. The state will also help the township and village tree 
farms to transform themselves into shareholding enterprises to 
benefit local farmers. 

</TEXT>

