<H3> <TI>   Jiang, Others Meet Air Force Representatives </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0201043494 Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service in Chinese 1004 
GMT 24 Dec 93 </F>

<F P=103> OW0201043494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Sun Maoqing (1327 5399 1987)] </F>
  [Text] Beijing, 24 Dec (XINHUA) -- Central Military 
Commission [CMC] Chairman Jiang Zemin; Vice Chairmen Liu Huaqing 
and Zhang Zhen; members Chi Haotian, Zhang Wannian, Yu Yongbo, 
and Fu Quanyou; and leaders from the PLA [People's Liberation 
Army] General Staff Department, General Political Department, 
and General Logistics Department met today at the Great Hall of 
the People with representatives who are attending the Air 
Force's Eighth Party Congress. 
  At around 1400, Jiang Zemin, along with other CMC leaders, 
stepped into the Great Hall amid warm applause. Jiang Zemin 
elatedly and warmly greeted Air Force's party congress 
representatives. He wished the congress success. He also 
conveyed warm greetings to all who work at the forefront of the 
Air Force's modernization construction and wished all a happy 
new year. 

