<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Airport Operates `Safely' for 5 Years </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401033894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0230 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401033894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 4 (XINHUA) -- The Hongqiao 
International Airport in this China's largest economic center 
has operated safely for five years running. 
  A survey shows that the airport accommodated 63,000 planes 
and transported 7.6 million passengers last year without 
airport-related incidents. 
  An official of the airport attributed the good results to 
imposing ten measures to ensure safety and on-the-job 
responsibility. 
  While reinforcing safety checks and inviting specialists to 
give lectures, airport authorities have increased the number of 
tours of inspection at the airport. 
  Last year the airport handled 1,310 passengers with 
incomplete boarding papers and false identity cards as well as 
193 persons without tickets. Numerous contraband goods were 
also confiscated. 

</TEXT>

