<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Telecommunications Industry Expanding </TI></H3>
<H4>   Offers More Services </H4>
<F P=102> OW0401034194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0234 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401034194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, January 4 (XINHUA) -- The 
Telecommunications Department of Guangzhou, capital of south 
China's Guangdong Province, is offering a dozen new services to 
customers. 
  The city has opened China's largest video telecommunications 
system, telephone post boxes and videophone service. 
  Recently the city's "108" station began to handle 
international collect calls. 
  People can use an ordinary telephone to dial 1-0-8 and the 
number of the expected country and region, and the operator will 
switch to the receiver, who pays the toll. At present, the 
service covers the United States, Japan, Singapore, Italy and 
the Republic of Korea. 
  In addition, Guangzhou residents can also make long-distance 
calls on any phones just by dialing their own account number and 
cipher, and the charge will be assessed automatically by the 
computer system. 

</TEXT>

