<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Agricultural Output Increases </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK0401150094 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1420 GMT 
4 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK0401150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, January 4 (CNS) -- The total 
agricultural production of Guangdong Province in 1993 is 
expected to show a three percent increase over 1992 and the per 
capita year-round income of farmers in the province will reach 
RMB [renminbi] 1,600, RMB 292 over that earned in 1992, 
accounting for an increase of eight percent, taking the 
inflationary rise into consideration. 
  According to incomplete statistics, the area under rice 
cultivation in the province last year was 2.6 million hectares, 
with 48 percent of the harvest of high quality and an increase 
of 30 percentage points over the previous year. 
  The province gave much attention to the introduction of high 
quality livestock with 18,000 breeding hens, 28,000 breeding 
ducks and a number of breeding pigs brought into the province 
during last year. The ratio of lean meat of pigs to fat meat 
increased from 35 percent to 50 percent. 

</TEXT>

