<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hijacker Sentenced to 9 Years in Taiwan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0501111694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1106 GMT 5 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0501111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, January 5 (XINHUA) -- Zhang Wenlong, who 
hijacked a plane from the Chinese mainland to Taiwan on June 4 
last year, was sentenced to nine years' imprisonment by a local 
Taiwan court Tuesday [4 January]. 
  According to Taiwan newspapers, the Taiwan procurators in 
Taoyuan also instituted proceedings yesterday against Zhang Hai, 
Han Shuxue and Li Xiangyu, who also hijacked mainland planes to 
Taiwan last year, and demanded imprisonment of over 12 years for 
them. 
  Previously, some Taiwan media and public figures had urged 
that the hijackers should all be sent back to the mainland, 
where they should be sentenced to death or life-long prison 
terms without probation, according to China's laws. 

</TEXT>

