<H3> <TI>   Ministry `Declined to Confirm' Lesotho Ties Break </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401151094 Taipei CNA in English 1406 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lillian Lin] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, Jan. 4 (CNA) -- The Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs Tuesday [4 January] declined to confirm a report that 
Lesotho will sever its diplomatic relations with the Republic of 
China [ROC], though the ministry would not rule out the 
possibility. 
  A ministry source said that relations between the ROC and 
Lesotho ran into difficulties last April, when Lesotho's new 
administration enthusiastically sought to establish close ties 
with Beijing. 
  The Foreign Affairs Ministry is still trying to safeguard 
the 
existing relationship, according to the source, who said the ROC 
Embassy in Lesotho is still in operation. 
  He said the reported diplomatic breakup could be confirmed 
after the end of New Year's celebrations in the African country. 

</TEXT>

