<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Investment Planned for 3 Gorges Project </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401135994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1352 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401135994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yichang, January 4 (XINHUA) -- China plans to 
increase the investment in the preparatory work of the Three 
Gorges project in 1994, an official said here today. 
  He Gong, deputy general manager of the Three Gorges Project 
Development Corporation, told XINHUA that 1994 will be the first 
year to see large-scale digging and other preparatory 
construction work for the project. 
  The manager did not release the exact amount to be 
increased. 
  Currently, he said, all the preparatory work, including 
earth 
and rock work on the southern bank of the river, a 
specially-built highway and a highway bridge across the Chang 
Jiang river has started. 
  Also, included are construction of on-site transportation 
work, power supply, heating, telecommunications and 
accommodation for the workers. 
  He said that his corporation will also invite public bidding 
nationwide for this year's preparatory work and will select high 
efficient construction companies for the work. 

</TEXT>

