<H3> <TI>   Baoshan Iron, Steel Plant Beats Production Target </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW0401103194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0955 GMT 4 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW0401103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, January 4 (XINHUA) -- The Baoshan Iron and 
Steel Plant in Shanghai, the most modern steel producer in 
China, has beaten its 1993 production targets, according to 
latest statistics. 
  In 1993, Baoshan produced 7.22 million tons of steel, an 
increase of 7.55 percent over the previous year, and 6.57 
million tons of iron, an increase of 5.47 percent over the 
previous year. 
  It reported a sales volume of 17.5 billion yuan and its 
profits and taxes grew by 110 percent. 
  According to its officials, the plant plans to produce 7.5 
million tons of steel in 1994 and products of high added value 
will account for one-third of the total output. 

