<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   BOC Hong Kong Branch Finances Mainland Projects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WA0501194594 Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO in Chinese 3 Nov 93 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> WA0501194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong TA KUNG PAO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Summary] The Bank of China Group is continuing to finance 
mainland infrastructure projects in the energy, transport, 
telecommunications, and raw material sectors as "supply 
shortages" in these areas were slowing economic development. 
According to the group's general manager in Hong Kong, the Bank 
of China is now directly involved in over 2,500 projects on the 
mainland and has advanced $7 billion in loans, 39 percent of 
which are directed to energy projects such as the Daya Bay 
Nuclear Power Plant. 

</TEXT>

